    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This property contains the button's key equivalent, or the empty string if no equivalent has been defined. Buttons don’t have a default key equivalent."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you set a key equivalent instead of an image, the button’s interior is redrawn. However, the key equivalent isn’t displayed if the image position is set to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSNoImage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSImageOnly"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", or "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSImageOverlaps"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "; that is, the button must display both its title and its “image” (which is the key equivalent in this case), and they must not overlap."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To display a key equivalent on a button, set the image and alternate image to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "nil"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", set the key equivalent, and then set the image position."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
